Tattvaa Yogashala offers the opportunity to journey into the depths of your yoga practice. Located in Rishikesh, the yoga capital of the world, on the banks of the holy Ganges River, our school offers a natural haven for those who seek an experience and environment in which to evolve in body, mind and spirit. We are globally known for world class Yoga Teacher Training in Rishikesh, India. Tattvaa Yogashala is a world renown yoga school specialising in the traditional Ashtanga system of yoga. I am now ready for Day 24 in your 30 day HOME series!!!  I am loving every morning :)  I am almosty 64...and I have been practicing yoga (on and some off) since 1997.  My yoga happy-place is Kripalu in Massachusetts :)  I knew I needed instruction, accountability, and challenge.  I lost my mom in February of 2019 (we were buddies)...and this last year has been one of busyness, some weight gain, and a diagnosis of a hiatal hernia (small), GERD, and some esophageal inflammation.  I am on a safe med for the GERD...and my vegan diet is serving me well.   But the yoga!!!!  with you!!!   About two weeks into the series, I realized I was heartburn-symptom-free :)   Now, I'm not sure it's the yoga...and you...but I'm thinking there's a connection :)  My husband and I spent the night in Austin in late December...on our way to my nephew in San Antonio.  If I EVER return to Austin...I would love to take a live class with you.   You have been perfect for me...the right amount of challenge and rest, your loving style, your voice...    I just HAD to let you know how I feel!   Blessings coming your way from South Bend, Indiana :)   P. S.  :)  I forget to mention how much stronger and steadier I am feeling!

It's late May and we've been sheltering at home since March 15. I discovered Yoga with Adriene when I was looking for some online yoga videos because my neck was getting really bad and my pants were getting tight from all the snacking while working from home! I used to do in person yoga classes but it's been several years (and I wasn't much more than a beginner then) because I went back to school and I still do work and school full time. Also... just starting menopause.  Anyhow, this "return" thing instead of "transform" is an interesting concept and it was hard for me to get there. But now instead of obsessing over how my body is changing for the better I am focusing on making peace with my body and making peace with getting older.  Oh, and after today's practice I went from barely being able to move my head from neck pain to total full movement with absolutely no pain - not even a twinge. Miraculous.

Here's a little something to deepen the idea of focus:
"Focus" in Latin translates to "HEARTH".  
And the goddess of the hearth was Vesta.. Hestia for the Greeks.
She was not personified (no statues) but rather an imaginal figure.
Here's what Barbara Kirksey concludes in her essay on Hestia:
"As part of the archetype of the journey home to the hearth,
focusing is the experience of and connection to Hestia,
builder of the house, so that the soul may dream in peace."

The practices from the past couple of days have really left me in a blissful state! I can feel my heart opening each time I step onto the mat which then helps me to consciously open my heart off of the mat! Through this journey I have reconnected with family I previously would not speak to. As they are known to have abusive tendencies. I had a disagreement with one of those family members last night and in this disagreement I actually forgot that when people dont get what they want they tend to hold onto it and carry a sense of heaviness because it is hard to release negativity. Having been on my spiritual path for a couple years it's become common place for me to communicate what i need and i am not scared to set my boundaries with people who once terrified me. It's just interesting to me how behaviors that were once so common to my state being are now coming up in others and i am seeing their heart closed, heavy and unwavering in this sorrow the body insists on holding onto for dear life. I am proud of myself and I feel through embracing connections with those I can only love from a distance that I am learning not only about how I used to be with a new sense of clarity but I am learning I have grown stronger in the work I have been doing to consciously soften. I dont worry about judgement from these beings anymore, I dont make myself small for anyone anymore and it is so empowering to see the evidence of this. I wouldn't be on this journey if I hadn't found YWA over two years ago, so thank you for carving your light into the world. It has made such a difference for me on my journey. Namaste 🕉🙏
